SIMPLE: retrace
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retrace
<hw>Re*trace"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re-</ets> + <ets>trace</ets>: cf. F. <ets>retracer</ets>. Cf.
<er>Retract</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To trace back, as a
line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then if the line of Turnus you <qex>retrace</qex>,⟦br⟧
He springs from Inachus of Argive race.</q>
<rj><qau>Driden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To go back, in or over (a previous course); to go
over again in a reverse direction; <as>as, to <ex>retrace</ex> one's
steps; to <ex>retrace</ex> one's proceedings.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To trace over again, or renew the outline of, as a
drawing; to draw again.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retract</ent>⟦br⟧
